=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Use 2-amino-4,6-dichlorophenol and the chiral side-chain precursor (R)-1-Boc-pyrrolidine-3-carboxylic acid (or make it by Boc-protecting (R)-pyrrolidine-3-carboxylic acid). | Step 2: Couple 2-amino-4,6-dichlorophenol with (R)-1-Boc-pyrrolidine-3-carboxylic acid under amide-bond-forming conditions (e.g., CDI or EDC/HOBt, DIPEA) to give N-[(2-hydroxy-3,5-dichlorophenyl)]-(R)-1-Boc-pyrrolidine-3-carboxamide. | Step 3: Cyclodehydrate this o-hydroxy amide (e.g., POCl3 or PPA) to form 4,6-dichloro-2-[(R)-1-Boc-pyrrolidin-3-yl]benzo[d]oxazole. | Step 4: Remove Boc with TFA/CH2Cl2 or HCl/dioxane to unveil the free secondary amine and obtain the target Clc1cc2oc([C@H]3CCCN3)cc2nc1Cl.

